President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Albert Beveridge, Constance Carroll, and Cathy Davidson to key administration posts on the National Council on the Humanities. Albert Beveridge is a founding member and Senior Counsel of the law firm of Beveridge & Diamond, P.C and has served as General Counsel of the American Historical Association. Constance Carroll has served as Chancellor of the San Diego Community College District and has board service in various organizations. Cathy Davidson is a professor at Duke University and co-founder of HASTAC, a network of educators focused on new modes of learning for the digital age.